Global Emissions EDGAR v4.2 (November 2011)
In EDGARv4.2 emissions are calculated for
(1) direct greenhouse gases, (2) ozone precursor gases and (3) acidifying gases. 
For each group an overview table presents the status of data available for download.
https://edgar.jrc.ec.europa.eu/overview.php?v=42

Greenhouse gas emission statistics - emission inventories
https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/statistics-explained/index.php/Greenhouse_gas_emission_statistics

The Odyssee database contains detailed energy consumption by end-use and their drivers as well as
energy efficiency and CO2 related indicators. Latest available data is providing by national representatives,
such as energy agencies or statistical organization, from all EU countries as well as Norway, Switzerland and Serbia.
https://www.indicators.odyssee-mure.eu/energy-efficiency-database.html

